1
00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:42,959
l have a friend, Deborah,
a psychologist...

2
00:00:43,127 --> 00:00:45,294
...who was asked
by the city of Philadelphia...

3
00:00:45,462 --> 00:00:49,549
...if she could offer psychological
counseling to Cambodian refugees...

4
00:00:49,717 --> 00:00:53,261
...boat people,
who had recently arrived in the city.

5
00:00:53,429 --> 00:00:56,556
Deborah was daunted by the task.
These Cambodians...

6
00:00:56,724 --> 00:01:01,728
...had suffered genocide, starvation,
relatives murdered before their eyes...

7
00:01:01,895 --> 00:01:05,648
...years in refugee camps,
harrowing boat trips to the West.

8
00:01:06,108 --> 00:01:07,984
How could she relate
to their suffering?

9
00:01:08,152 --> 00:01:09,819
How could she help these people?

10
00:01:16,201 --> 00:01:18,703
So guess what all these people
wanted to talk about...

11
00:01:18,871 --> 00:01:21,622
...with my friend Deborah,
the psychologist.

12
00:01:23,709 --> 00:01:26,544
lt was all,
"l met this guy in the refugee camp.

13
00:01:26,712 --> 00:01:29,547
I thought he really loved me,
but when we got separated...

14
00:01:29,715 --> 00:01:32,300
...he took up with my cousin.
Now he says he loves me...

15
00:01:32,468 --> 00:01:35,928
...and keeps calling me. They're
married now. What should l do?"

16
00:01:36,096 --> 00:01:37,180
This is how we are.

17
00:01:37,347 --> 00:01:38,556
May I help you?

18
00:01:38,724 --> 00:01:41,392
I'm Liz Gilbert. I'm writing
a magazine article on Bali.

19
00:01:41,560 --> 00:01:43,019
I wanted to meet a medicine man.

20
00:01:43,187 --> 00:01:46,272
Everyone said I should meet
Ketut Liyer. Am l in the right place?

21
00:01:46,440 --> 00:01:47,523
Wait.

22
00:01:47,691 --> 00:01:52,028
l mean, here I am with
a ninth-generation medicine man...

23
00:01:52,196 --> 00:01:54,697
...and what do I wanna
ask him about?

24
00:01:54,865 --> 00:01:57,200
Getting closer to God?

25
00:01:57,367 --> 00:02:00,912
Saving the world's
starving children?

26
00:02:01,663 --> 00:02:04,207
Happy to see you. l am Ketut Liyer.

27
00:02:04,374 --> 00:02:09,295
Nope. l wanna discuss
my relationship.

28
00:02:12,591 --> 00:02:15,134
You are a world traveler.

29
00:02:15,302 --> 00:02:17,386
You will live a long time...

30
00:02:17,554 --> 00:02:20,890
...have many friends,
many experiences.

31
00:02:22,476 --> 00:02:26,145
You will have two marriages.
One long, one short.

32
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:28,272
Am l in the long one
or the short one?

33
00:02:28,816 --> 00:02:30,358
Can't tell.

34
00:02:30,526 --> 00:02:34,487
Also you will lose all your money.

35
00:02:35,572 --> 00:02:38,825
I think in next six to 1 0 months.

36
00:02:40,118 --> 00:02:43,204
Don't worry.
You will get it all back again.

37
00:02:43,914 --> 00:02:46,290
And you will come back to Bali...

38
00:02:46,458 --> 00:02:52,755
...and live here for three or four
months and teach me English.

39
00:02:52,923 --> 00:02:56,384
I never had anybody
to practice my English with.

40
00:02:57,135 --> 00:02:58,719
And then...

41
00:02:58,887 --> 00:03:04,267
...l will teach you everything l know.

42
00:03:07,104 --> 00:03:08,938
Wait.

43
00:03:13,151 --> 00:03:15,069
I have this for you.

44
00:03:15,237 --> 00:03:18,698
Keep grounded so it's like
you have four legs.

45
00:03:19,116 --> 00:03:21,367
That way, you can stay in this world.

46
00:03:21,952 --> 00:03:25,913
Also, no looking at world
through your head.

47
00:03:26,081 --> 00:03:28,499
Look through your heart instead.

48
00:03:28,667 --> 00:03:30,793
That way, you will know God.

49
00:03:32,254 --> 00:03:34,463
Which is why you came here, no?

50
00:03:35,632 --> 00:03:39,051
See you later, alligator.

51
00:03:53,442 --> 00:03:56,819
I proofread all of her manuscripts.

52
00:03:56,987 --> 00:04:00,489
My wife is very, very beautiful,
but she can't spell for anything.

53
00:04:00,657 --> 00:04:03,326
Look at Uncle Stephen.

54
00:04:04,828 --> 00:04:05,995
And Auntie Liz.

55
00:04:06,163 --> 00:04:09,874
I'm counting the minutes for this to be
over so l can get in my big girl pants.

56
00:04:10,042 --> 00:04:12,001
You look fantastic.
You just had a baby.

57
00:04:12,169 --> 00:04:14,170
Oh, you're lying.
I'm fat, I'm exhausted...

58
00:04:14,338 --> 00:04:16,881
...l can't keep two thoughts.
I feel like Liza Minnelli.

59
00:04:17,049 --> 00:04:18,716
Stephen, can you hold Jack?

60
00:04:18,884 --> 00:04:21,218
-l'm gonna introduce you to Walter.
-Yeah.

61
00:04:22,012 --> 00:04:25,431
Hey, dude, you wanna grab a beer
or something?

62
00:04:25,682 --> 00:04:28,309
My new book comes out in April.
Thank you for asking.

63
00:04:28,477 --> 00:04:29,518
-Great.
-May.

64
00:04:29,686 --> 00:04:31,020
May. May.

65
00:04:31,688 --> 00:04:34,482
This is Andre. You two are
Times' Most Notable nominees.

66
00:04:34,650 --> 00:04:37,360
-So glad to finally meet you.
-Nice to finally meet you.

67
00:04:39,363 --> 00:04:41,072
I fed him nachos. ls that bad?

68
00:04:41,239 --> 00:04:43,741
You look comfortable.
What'd you feed him, chloroform?

69
00:04:43,909 --> 00:04:45,868
-Give him to his dad.
-l told you, nachos.

70
00:04:46,036 --> 00:04:48,579
Know what? I'd be asleep too
if l had a dump like that.

71
00:04:48,747 --> 00:04:51,749
-We'll give him to his mom.
-Come here then.

72
00:04:53,377 --> 00:04:55,503
-Wanna help me change his diaper?
-Yes, I do.

73
00:04:55,671 --> 00:04:57,546
Hey, how's the vintage car
thing going?

74
00:04:57,714 --> 00:05:00,508
Oh, no, no, no. l changed jobs.
I'm a pastry chef now.

75
00:05:00,676 --> 00:05:02,802
-You mean you're a baker.
-Yeah.

76
00:05:02,970 --> 00:05:04,720
You wanna get baked?

77
00:05:06,223 --> 00:05:08,849
I know, I know.

78
00:05:09,017 --> 00:05:11,060
It's hard, isn't it?

79
00:05:11,561 --> 00:05:15,356
Oh, no. This is so much fun.

80
00:05:15,899 --> 00:05:18,526
Did you know the exact moment
you wanted to have a baby?

81
00:05:18,694 --> 00:05:23,197
I can't remember, but l've had the box
since before l got married.

82
00:05:23,365 --> 00:05:24,907
What box?

83
00:05:25,075 --> 00:05:28,202
It's girly and embarrassing,
and you'll laugh at me if I tell you.

84
00:05:28,662 --> 00:05:31,664
I will laugh at you,
but you still have to tell me.

85
00:05:32,249 --> 00:05:34,000
Come on.

86
00:05:34,668 --> 00:05:36,168
Under the bed.

87
00:05:42,551 --> 00:05:45,261
I've been filling it with baby things...

88
00:05:45,429 --> 00:05:48,264
...waiting until Andy
was ready to be a father.

89
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:53,227
So sweet.

90
00:05:53,395 --> 00:05:55,062
Does this come in my size?

91
00:06:01,111 --> 00:06:04,613
I have a box just like this, except
it's filled with National Geographics...

92
00:06:04,781 --> 00:06:06,949
...and The Times travel section.

93
00:06:07,117 --> 00:06:10,244
All the places l wanna see
before l die.

94
00:06:10,412 --> 00:06:14,874
Liz, having a baby is like
getting a tattoo on your face.

95
00:06:16,293 --> 00:06:18,461
You kind of wanna be
fully committed.

96
00:06:22,424 --> 00:06:25,801
So my trip to Aruba next week,
which is just a basic, you know...

97
00:06:25,969 --> 00:06:28,596
..."where to sleep, swim
and stuff your face" piece....

98
00:06:28,764 --> 00:06:30,222
I got a new bikini.

99
00:06:30,390 --> 00:06:33,893
And it turns out,
I have unlimited minibar access.

100
00:06:34,061 --> 00:06:35,895
-You know what that means?
-Jet lag?

101
00:06:36,063 --> 00:06:38,773
You, me...

102
00:06:38,940 --> 00:06:40,316
...macadamia nuts.

103
00:06:41,860 --> 00:06:42,943
That was cute.

104
00:06:43,111 --> 00:06:46,322
You know who l was talking to
at the party who was really inspiring...

105
00:06:46,490 --> 00:06:47,865
-...was Tara's friend.
-Brian.

106
00:06:48,033 --> 00:06:51,202
Brian. Unbelievable.
He's a teacher, you know that?

107
00:06:51,369 --> 00:06:53,120
He's a substitute teacher, isn't he?

108
00:06:53,288 --> 00:06:56,332
Yeah. He was talking about the
budget cuts that are happening now.

109
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:58,250
There's no money for anything.

110
00:06:58,418 --> 00:07:01,087
There's no music classes,
there's no arts classes.

111
00:07:01,254 --> 00:07:04,215
They're volunteering their time
to do all of this after school.

112
00:07:04,382 --> 00:07:06,425
They're educating our kids,
you know?

113
00:07:06,593 --> 00:07:09,470
I think you'd make
a great teacher, honey.

114
00:07:09,638 --> 00:07:12,848
Thank you,
but I was thinking more of like...

115
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:16,769
...education. Getting my masters,
going back to school. l don't know.

116
00:07:16,937 --> 00:07:18,604
You know?

117
00:07:25,362 --> 00:07:27,488
I-- You know....

118
00:07:28,115 --> 00:07:30,699
-Going back to school.
-l'm just thinking out loud.

119
00:07:33,245 --> 00:07:38,290
I was getting the sinking feeling that
Ketut's prophecy was coming true.

120
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:41,127
Was l in the shorter marriage?

121
00:07:42,879 --> 00:07:45,881
We'd only bought this house
a year ago.

122
00:07:46,550 --> 00:07:47,967
Hadn't I wanted this?

123
00:07:50,428 --> 00:07:54,723
I had actively participated
in every moment of the creation...

124
00:07:54,891 --> 00:07:56,725
...of this life.

125
00:07:56,893 --> 00:08:00,229
So why didn't I see myself
in any of it?

126
00:08:05,652 --> 00:08:09,572
The only thing more impossible
than staying...

127
00:08:09,739 --> 00:08:11,615
...was leaving.

128
00:08:13,243 --> 00:08:17,413
I didn't wanna hurt anybody. l wanted
to slip quietly out the back door...

129
00:08:17,581 --> 00:08:21,083
...and not stop running
until l reached Greenland.

130
00:08:25,547 --> 00:08:28,090
lnstead, l made a decision.

131
00:08:28,717 --> 00:08:30,426
To pray.

132
00:08:30,677 --> 00:08:34,096
You know, like, to God.

133
00:08:34,806 --> 00:08:39,351
And it was such a foreign concept to
me, that l swear l almost began with:

134
00:08:39,519 --> 00:08:41,520
"l'm a big fan of your work."

135
00:08:48,737 --> 00:08:50,821
Hello, God?

136
00:08:53,700 --> 00:08:56,785
Nice to finally meet you. l....

137
00:08:57,704 --> 00:09:03,959
I am sorry l've never spoken
directly to you before...

138
00:09:04,127 --> 00:09:05,794
...but...

139
00:09:06,630 --> 00:09:09,465
...l hope l've expressed my...

140
00:09:10,133 --> 00:09:14,178
...ample gratitude for all
the blessings you've given...

141
00:09:14,346 --> 00:09:16,639
...to me in my life.

142
00:09:26,483 --> 00:09:28,984
I'm in serious trouble.

143
00:09:30,987 --> 00:09:33,322
I don't know what to do.

144
00:09:34,658 --> 00:09:37,159
I need an answer.

145
00:09:37,661 --> 00:09:41,872
Please, tell me what to do.

146
00:09:43,416 --> 00:09:46,335
Oh, God, help me, please.

147
00:09:52,509 --> 00:09:55,469
Tell me what to do and l'll do it.

148
00:09:58,306 --> 00:10:01,016
Go back to bed, Liz.

149
00:10:22,414 --> 00:10:24,373
I don't wanna go to Aruba.

150
00:10:28,003 --> 00:10:30,629
I don't wanna be married.

151
00:10:47,939 --> 00:10:50,733
You know, there's a whole
divorce section downstairs.

152
00:11:09,502 --> 00:11:11,086
-"Pepper grinder."
-She's having...

153
00:11:11,254 --> 00:11:13,464
-...a nervous breakdown.
-This is what girls do.

154
00:11:13,631 --> 00:11:16,133
-She's processing.
-Why doesn't she get drunk or laid?

155
00:11:16,301 --> 00:11:18,302
That's what l would do if you left me.

156
00:11:18,470 --> 00:11:19,845
No, you wouldn't.

157
00:11:20,013 --> 00:11:22,723
-No, I wouldn't.
-She moved out, she filed for divorce.

158
00:11:22,891 --> 00:11:26,185
They were together eight years.
She's got no home.

159
00:11:33,276 --> 00:11:35,194
"Legacy."

160
00:11:37,781 --> 00:11:42,618
Every word in Italian is like a truffle.
A magic trick.

161
00:11:43,119 --> 00:11:46,163
Honey, l get it.
It's your life raft right now.

162
00:11:46,331 --> 00:11:49,583
When Andy and l broke up
for two weeks, l bought a loom.

163
00:11:49,751 --> 00:11:52,586
A frigging loom.
And he tried to start a microbrewery.

164
00:11:52,754 --> 00:11:55,714
I don't know how you guys
aren't sick of me now. I'm sick of me.

165
00:11:55,882 --> 00:11:58,133
Are you kidding me?
We love having you.

166
00:11:58,301 --> 00:12:00,427
It's kind of like having
a writer in residence.

167
00:12:00,595 --> 00:12:03,097
But you are a writer.
You should be writing something.

168
00:12:03,264 --> 00:12:07,434
Maybe I could write about a woman
who goes to Italy to learn ltalian.

169
00:12:07,602 --> 00:12:11,063
Call it
Carbohydrates and Conjugations.

170
00:12:11,231 --> 00:12:13,774
I'll start looking for a place.

171
00:12:15,527 --> 00:12:18,237
-l'm falling in love with you.
-l'm not who you think I am.

172
00:12:18,405 --> 00:12:19,905
I'm just your fantasy.

173
00:12:20,073 --> 00:12:24,284
No, that's bullshit. You're real.

174
00:12:25,161 --> 00:12:27,454
Your scars, your talent.

175
00:12:27,622 --> 00:12:29,706
The fact that
I own a piece-of-crap bar...

176
00:12:29,874 --> 00:12:32,126
...and you accept that
that's all l'm gonna do.

177
00:12:32,293 --> 00:12:33,669
Okay, this sucks.

178
00:12:33,837 --> 00:12:36,338
-l second that.
-Don't be rude.

179
00:12:43,430 --> 00:12:45,556
I love your pain.

180
00:12:46,307 --> 00:12:50,269
And l love that when we're together,
I can make it go away.

181
00:12:51,354 --> 00:12:52,855
-Oh, he's good.
-You're love...

182
00:12:53,022 --> 00:12:56,692
-He's hot, there's a difference.
-...is like a hot panini.

183
00:12:56,860 --> 00:13:01,989
And when I look into your eyes,
I hear dolphins clapping.

184
00:13:02,157 --> 00:13:04,658
I did not write that line.

185
00:13:04,826 --> 00:13:06,326
Here's what he doesn't know yet.

186
00:13:07,579 --> 00:13:11,290
I disappear into the person l love.

187
00:13:11,458 --> 00:13:16,378
I am the permeable membrane.
If l love you, you can have it all.

188
00:13:16,546 --> 00:13:19,381
My money, my time, my body...

189
00:13:19,549 --> 00:13:23,051
...my dog, my dog's money.

190
00:13:23,219 --> 00:13:26,388
I will assume your debts
and project upon you...

191
00:13:26,556 --> 00:13:31,727
...all sorts of nifty qualities you've
never actually cultivated in yourself.

192
00:13:31,895 --> 00:13:34,480
I will give you all this and more...

193
00:13:34,647 --> 00:13:37,483
...until l am so exhausted
and depleted...

194
00:13:37,650 --> 00:13:40,486
...the only way l can recover...

195
00:13:40,653 --> 00:13:43,197
...is by becoming infatuated
with someone else.

196
00:13:50,413 --> 00:13:52,623
-Elizabeth, hi.
-Hi.

197
00:13:52,790 --> 00:13:54,416
Oh, really?

198
00:13:57,337 --> 00:13:59,421
How you doing?

199
00:14:30,703 --> 00:14:32,454
Cheers.

200
00:14:34,123 --> 00:14:36,583
-Thank you.
-l owe you an apology.

201
00:14:36,751 --> 00:14:40,629
-For the walkouts.
-Well, l'm not everyone's cup of tea.

202
00:14:41,381 --> 00:14:43,340
I doubt that.

203
00:14:44,092 --> 00:14:46,093
I, on the other hand, was shit.

204
00:14:46,886 --> 00:14:51,640
-Although l was trying very hard.
-"Shit" is a strong word.

205
00:14:52,308 --> 00:14:53,517
Thank you.

206
00:14:53,685 --> 00:14:56,645
You seem shorter in person
than on the stage.

207
00:14:56,813 --> 00:14:58,730
-Really? l hear that a lot.
-Sorry.

208
00:14:58,898 --> 00:15:00,440
It's okay.

209
00:15:01,234 --> 00:15:03,360
It's unnerving when...

210
00:15:03,528 --> 00:15:07,489
...a total stranger sees you
more clearly than you see yourself.

211
00:15:07,657 --> 00:15:09,908
That's what l mean
by saying you're short.

212
00:15:14,330 --> 00:15:17,583
Are you hearing dolphins clapping
right now?

213
00:15:18,918 --> 00:15:22,337
I took a few liberties
with your material.

214
00:15:22,505 --> 00:15:25,799
I give you full permission to make
fun of me. I know you're dying to.

215
00:15:27,510 --> 00:15:30,387
You're far too charming
to make fun of.

216
00:15:34,767 --> 00:15:37,019
I'm still hearing them.

217
00:15:45,987 --> 00:15:48,322
Is that your guru?

218
00:15:49,407 --> 00:15:52,284
You're joking, but, yes, it is.

219
00:15:53,578 --> 00:15:55,495
She's beautiful.

220
00:15:55,663 --> 00:15:58,332
Yeah. A friend told me about her.

221
00:15:59,208 --> 00:16:02,127
I was out of work and feeling
pretty desperate for something.

222
00:16:02,295 --> 00:16:05,130
Not the last time I was out of work,
the time before that.

223
00:16:05,298 --> 00:16:10,552
And l just had this feeling like
I was looking in all the wrong places.

224
00:16:10,720 --> 00:16:11,970
Looking for what?

225
00:16:12,305 --> 00:16:13,347
God.

226
00:16:14,932 --> 00:16:18,268
She has an ashram in India.
I'm dying to go, but...

227
00:16:18,436 --> 00:16:21,772
...you know, you have to get, like,
three stages of hepatitis shots...

228
00:16:21,939 --> 00:16:24,816
...and my insurance always runs out.

229
00:16:25,026 --> 00:16:26,943
I'll go when the time's right.

230
00:16:27,111 --> 00:16:30,280
There's a gathering of her students
every morning.

231
00:16:31,407 --> 00:16:34,409
If you want,
I could take you sometime.

232
00:16:34,577 --> 00:16:39,915
If you're not unnerved by 1 00
crunchy people chanting in Sanskrit.

233
00:16:40,750 --> 00:16:43,001
I need to be unnerved.

234
00:17:13,908 --> 00:17:17,577
David. A yogi from Yonkers.

235
00:17:19,122 --> 00:17:22,499
I didn't exactly fall in love
with the guy.

236
00:17:23,918 --> 00:17:26,586
What happened was
I dove out of my marriage...

237
00:17:26,754 --> 00:17:28,380
...and into David's arms...

238
00:17:28,548 --> 00:17:31,800
...exactly the same way
a cartoon circus performer...

239
00:17:31,968 --> 00:17:36,596
...dives off a high platform
and into a small cup of water...

240
00:17:37,014 --> 00:17:38,473
...vanishing completely.

241
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:50,068
Your underwear, my queen.

242
00:17:53,656 --> 00:17:56,241
He just folded my delicates.

243
00:17:56,409 --> 00:18:00,120
Oh, my God, baby,
you are in so much trouble.

244
00:18:52,173 --> 00:18:53,548
Thirty-six?

245
00:19:07,230 --> 00:19:09,731
My client is simply not interested
in a divorce.

246
00:19:11,609 --> 00:19:13,777
Is he serious?

247
00:19:13,945 --> 00:19:15,821
Is he really representing himself?

248
00:19:15,988 --> 00:19:18,073
One semester of law school
right here, baby.

249
00:19:18,241 --> 00:19:20,992
Great. Well, what would it take
to interest your client?

250
00:19:21,577 --> 00:19:24,746
Okay, so here's the deal.
You have screwed up my life...

251
00:19:24,914 --> 00:19:27,791
...but what l wanna know
is why couldn't you find yourself...

252
00:19:27,959 --> 00:19:30,836
...in our marriage? Why didn't you
say what you were thinking?

253
00:19:31,003 --> 00:19:33,505
-l did. You never listened to me.
-No. You never said:

254
00:19:33,673 --> 00:19:36,424
"Hey, you know what?
You suck. l'm deeply unhappy."

255
00:19:36,592 --> 00:19:39,928
You just took off. You never gave me
a chance to address those problems.

256
00:19:40,096 --> 00:19:42,931
That's not fair. That's just quitting.
I took vows.

257
00:19:43,099 --> 00:19:46,017
Till death.
And l take them seriously.

258
00:19:46,519 --> 00:19:49,396
I believe this is just a phase
and l'm willing to wait it out.

259
00:19:49,564 --> 00:19:51,022
You are always waiting, Stephen.

260
00:19:51,190 --> 00:19:53,441
Waiting for me to come home,
to wanna have kids...

261
00:19:53,609 --> 00:19:56,278
...to make you dinner.
I don't know why we can't accept...

262
00:19:56,445 --> 00:19:58,613
...we don't wanna live
in unhappiness anymore.

263
00:19:58,781 --> 00:20:01,283
I accept the fact that
I am occasionally unreliable...

264
00:20:01,450 --> 00:20:04,703
...and l often get sidetracked,
but I thought you liked that about me.

265
00:20:04,871 --> 00:20:07,205
I thought it was okay
that I had hopes and dreams.

266
00:20:07,373 --> 00:20:10,959
Have a dream. Stephen, great,
fine. Do that. Just pick one.

267
00:20:11,127 --> 00:20:13,128
Okay, l pick one. I pick you.

268
00:20:22,930 --> 00:20:25,348
I know this is awful.

269
00:20:26,726 --> 00:20:31,396
But l believe with every molecule of
my body that you will find the person...

270
00:20:31,564 --> 00:20:34,149
...that wants just what you want.

271
00:20:34,317 --> 00:20:37,652
That will give you what you want
and what you deserve. l'm not her.

272
00:20:38,070 --> 00:20:42,157
Well, you obviously know nothing
about what l want.

273
00:20:45,244 --> 00:20:47,495
My client would like to submit
a song he wrote...

274
00:20:47,663 --> 00:20:52,000
...that he believes is relevant to these
proceedings. Goes something like this:

275
00:20:53,002 --> 00:20:54,628
Are you kidding?

276
00:20:58,841 --> 00:21:01,134
Quitter, quitter, quitter!

277
00:21:01,302 --> 00:21:04,262
How about l take the blame?
I am the one who couldn't deal...

278
00:21:04,430 --> 00:21:07,432
...with another weekend roaming
some box-shaped superstore...

279
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:09,142
...buying appliances on credit...

280
00:21:09,310 --> 00:21:13,480
...and pretending to be a couple that
neither one of us ever knew how to be.

281
00:21:13,648 --> 00:21:15,023
You wanted that toaster.

282
00:21:15,191 --> 00:21:20,528
"You like faking it, fine. You're stellar.
I'm the failure. l suck at faking it."

283
00:21:20,863 --> 00:21:23,698
-lt was not my finest hour.
-So where do things stand now?

284
00:21:23,866 --> 00:21:26,284
We're prepared
to offer half of everything...

285
00:21:26,452 --> 00:21:29,496
...and my client's retirement accounts.

286
00:21:30,665 --> 00:21:32,874
Take it all then. Everything.

287
00:21:33,042 --> 00:21:35,377
He still said no.

288
00:21:35,878 --> 00:21:38,672
-He hates me now.
-He doesn't hate you.

289
00:21:38,839 --> 00:21:41,216
His heart is broken.

290
00:21:44,387 --> 00:21:45,887
I think he hates you.

291
00:21:46,055 --> 00:21:48,014
I'm never letting you
out of the basement.

292
00:21:48,182 --> 00:21:51,434
Why don't we talk next week
and we'll see where things stand?

293
00:21:51,602 --> 00:21:53,186
-Okay.
-These things have a way...

294
00:21:53,354 --> 00:21:54,980
...of working themselves out.

295
00:22:10,079 --> 00:22:11,830
So why'd you become a vegetarian?

296
00:22:11,998 --> 00:22:14,249
I saw some cows slaughtered
one time.

297
00:22:14,417 --> 00:22:16,251
Barely touched your dinner.

298
00:22:16,419 --> 00:22:18,753
He's 28.

299
00:22:21,590 --> 00:22:24,676
This is hard for him, isn't it?
And you?

300
00:22:24,844 --> 00:22:27,178
The meditations help.

301
00:22:28,472 --> 00:22:29,764
Liz.

302
00:22:30,141 --> 00:22:33,226
You remember a couple of years ago,
when you threw yourself into...

303
00:22:33,394 --> 00:22:36,062
...the renovation of your kitchen?
You were consumed...

304
00:22:36,230 --> 00:22:38,148
...with being the perfect wife and cook.

305
00:22:38,315 --> 00:22:39,733
I was trying to make it work.

306
00:22:39,900 --> 00:22:42,777
Well, l think chanting and meditation
is the same thing...

307
00:22:42,945 --> 00:22:44,612
...in a different costume.

308
00:22:48,242 --> 00:22:49,951
Definitely give me that documentary.

309
00:22:50,119 --> 00:22:52,078
I've been thinking
about vegetarianism.

310
00:22:52,246 --> 00:22:54,205
My triglycerides
are through the roof.

311
00:22:54,373 --> 00:22:55,707
Yeah. Thanks for everything.

312
00:22:55,875 --> 00:22:57,917
Great to meet you.

313
00:23:02,298 --> 00:23:06,176
-What?
-Nothing. lt's just...

314
00:23:06,343 --> 00:23:08,303
...you know,
you used to look like Stephen.

315
00:23:08,471 --> 00:23:10,805
Now you kind of look like David.

316
00:23:10,973 --> 00:23:12,599
You know?

317
00:23:13,392 --> 00:23:18,146
What l meant was, you know how
people start resembling their dogs?

318
00:23:20,649 --> 00:23:23,109
Why would he say that,
we look like the same dog?

319
00:23:23,277 --> 00:23:24,819
-He was joking.
-Not funny.

320
00:23:24,987 --> 00:23:27,530
Well, he had five Heinekens.
He was bombed.

321
00:23:27,698 --> 00:23:29,908
Well, not funny.

322
00:23:30,076 --> 00:23:32,535
We don't look like the same dog.

323
00:23:33,329 --> 00:23:38,792
If anything, you're a collie
and l'm a Tibetan mastiff.

324
00:23:48,928 --> 00:23:51,971
Don't you wanna give me a chance
to miss you?

325
00:24:13,202 --> 00:24:15,829
It begins when
the object of your affection...

326
00:24:15,996 --> 00:24:19,541
...bestows upon you
a heady hallucinogenic dose...

327
00:24:19,708 --> 00:24:22,710
...of something you've never
even dared to admit you wanted...

328
00:24:22,878 --> 00:24:26,798
...an emotional speedball
of thunderous love and excitement.

329
00:24:26,966 --> 00:24:30,260
Soon you start craving that attention
with the hungry obsession...

330
00:24:30,427 --> 00:24:32,053
...of any junkie.

331
00:24:32,221 --> 00:24:35,723
When it's withheld, you turn sick,
crazy, not to mention resentful...

332
00:24:35,891 --> 00:24:39,060
...of the dealer who encouraged
this addiction in the first place...

333
00:24:39,228 --> 00:24:41,604
...but now refuses to pony up
the good stuff.

334
00:24:41,772 --> 00:24:44,732
Just frustrated, l'm concerned.
I don't understand.

335
00:24:44,900 --> 00:24:46,401
What don't you get?

336
00:24:46,569 --> 00:24:48,653
What's going on?
You don't look me in the eye.

337
00:24:48,821 --> 00:24:51,197
-You don't finish your--
-Nobody's asking you to make the bed!

338
00:24:51,365 --> 00:24:54,117
-You don't have sex with me!
-Sometimes I'm not in the mood!

339
00:24:54,285 --> 00:24:56,911
Goddamn him, and he used to
give it to you for free.

340
00:24:57,079 --> 00:25:00,081
Next stage finds you skinny,
shaking in a corner...

341
00:25:00,249 --> 00:25:02,250
...certain only that
you'd sell your soul...

342
00:25:02,418 --> 00:25:04,502
...just to have that one thing
one more time.

343
00:25:04,670 --> 00:25:07,297
Well, then why don't we discuss it?
Why don't we sort it?

344
00:25:07,464 --> 00:25:10,800
-Why don't we act like adults?
-Okay. Can I have a little space?

345
00:25:10,968 --> 00:25:12,594
-How about that?
-Meanwhile...

346
00:25:12,761 --> 00:25:16,180
...the object of your adoration
is now repulsed by you.

347
00:25:16,348 --> 00:25:19,225
-You don't always make me miserable.
-There's a comfort.

348
00:25:19,393 --> 00:25:22,854
I just-- Sometimes l need to
come home...

349
00:25:23,522 --> 00:25:25,273
...and have a little David time.

350
00:25:25,441 --> 00:25:28,776
He looks at you like someone
he's never met before.

351
00:25:28,944 --> 00:25:30,695
-ls that okay?
-Yeah. No, it's fine.

352
00:25:30,863 --> 00:25:33,948
And not have to, like, you know,
justify it.

353
00:25:34,116 --> 00:25:37,243
The irony is
you can hardly blame him.

354
00:25:37,411 --> 00:25:40,788
I mean, check yourself out.
You're a mess.

355
00:25:40,956 --> 00:25:43,458
Unrecognizable
even to your own eyes.

356
00:25:43,626 --> 00:25:45,627
You asked me to come here?
Here l am.

357
00:25:45,794 --> 00:25:47,629
And it turned into something else.

358
00:25:47,796 --> 00:25:50,256
-Didn't it?
-You are such a child.

359
00:25:54,428 --> 00:25:57,805
-Right. I can't take this anymore.
-Great. Perfect.

360
00:25:57,973 --> 00:26:01,309
That's a great response
to a conversation.

361
00:26:01,477 --> 00:26:02,518
Goddamn it.

362
00:26:02,686 --> 00:26:07,607
You have now reached
infatuation's final destination.

363
00:26:08,484 --> 00:26:14,447
The complete
and merciless devaluation of self.

364
00:26:48,649 --> 00:26:50,024
You wanna go away for a year?

365
00:26:50,192 --> 00:26:52,318
Do you know what I felt
when l woke up, Delia?

366
00:26:52,486 --> 00:26:57,073
Nothing. No passion, no spark,
no faith, no heat. Absolutely nothing.

367
00:26:57,241 --> 00:27:00,451
I've gotten past the point where
I can be calling this a bad moment.

368
00:27:00,619 --> 00:27:03,955
And it just terrifies me. Jesus,
this is like worse than death to me...

369
00:27:04,123 --> 00:27:06,958
...the idea that this is the person
I'm gonna be from now on.

370
00:27:07,126 --> 00:27:08,418
This happens to people.

371
00:27:08,585 --> 00:27:10,670
They fall in love in their 20s,
get married...

372
00:27:10,838 --> 00:27:13,798
...do the granite countertop,
white-picket fence in their 30s...

373
00:27:13,966 --> 00:27:16,342
...and somewhere they realize,
"This is not for me."

374
00:27:16,510 --> 00:27:20,013
So they fail and they fall down,
they hurt like hell, they straighten up...

375
00:27:20,180 --> 00:27:22,432
...and march their asses
to the shrink's office.

376
00:27:22,599 --> 00:27:26,102
-They can't just check out.
-l am not checking out.

377
00:27:26,270 --> 00:27:27,770
I need to change.

378
00:27:27,938 --> 00:27:30,189
You have a support system
here, Liz.

379
00:27:30,357 --> 00:27:32,191
You have friends and family
who love you.

380
00:27:32,359 --> 00:27:36,029
And do you feel my love for you?
My support for you? No.

381
00:27:36,196 --> 00:27:38,698
There's, like, nothing. l have no pulse.

382
00:27:41,243 --> 00:27:43,661
-l am going to Italy.
-ltaly. Why ltaly?

383
00:27:43,829 --> 00:27:46,289
-What did you have for lunch?
-l don't know. A salad.

384
00:27:46,457 --> 00:27:51,669
Exactly. l used to have this appetite
for food, for my life...

385
00:27:51,837 --> 00:27:52,962
...and it is just gone.

386
00:27:54,548 --> 00:27:58,843
I wanna go someplace
where l can marvel at something.

387
00:27:59,011 --> 00:28:02,430
Language, gelato,
spaghetti, something.

388
00:28:02,598 --> 00:28:05,516
-You're talking like a college kid.
-l've been acting like one.

389
00:28:05,684 --> 00:28:09,228
Since I was 1 5, I've either been
with a guy or breaking up with a guy.

390
00:28:09,396 --> 00:28:12,356
I have not given myself
two weeks of a breather...

391
00:28:12,524 --> 00:28:15,818
...to just deal with, you know, myself.

392
00:28:18,155 --> 00:28:20,031
What's going on
with you and David?

393
00:28:28,665 --> 00:28:29,749
What, did you fall out?

394
00:28:30,084 --> 00:28:32,126
I don't know how to be here.

395
00:28:32,294 --> 00:28:35,922
You wanna know how to be here?
Stop constantly waiting for something.

396
00:28:40,594 --> 00:28:45,306
I'm going to Italy and then l'm going
to David's guru's ashram in lndia...

397
00:28:45,474 --> 00:28:48,893
...and l'm going to end the year
in Bali.

398
00:28:52,064 --> 00:28:53,439
That's what l'm gonna do.

399
00:28:53,607 --> 00:28:56,275
That's harder to argue with.
The beaches are nice. But why?

400
00:28:56,443 --> 00:28:58,444
-Ketut told me I would.
-Guy with no teeth.

401
00:28:58,612 --> 00:28:59,695
When you're desperate...

402
00:28:59,863 --> 00:29:02,365
...and some guy who,
yes, looks a little like Yoda...

403
00:29:02,533 --> 00:29:05,785
...hands you a prophecy,
you have to respond.

404
00:29:05,953 --> 00:29:08,121
-Do you need a Xanax?
-Always.

405
00:29:09,123 --> 00:29:12,458
Okay, l'm just gonna say it.
I'm gonna say it and be done with it.

406
00:29:12,626 --> 00:29:13,709
What if it doesn't work?

407
00:29:18,215 --> 00:29:21,050
My whole life
fits in a 1 2-foot-square box.

408
00:29:22,803 --> 00:29:25,471
You know how many times
I hear that in a day?

409
00:29:25,639 --> 00:29:27,932
Most of them never come back
for their whole life.

410
00:29:32,813 --> 00:29:33,980
-Hello?
-Liz.

411
00:29:34,148 --> 00:29:37,108
Good news. Stephen just signed
the divorce papers.

412
00:29:45,826 --> 00:29:50,037
I'll probably be back in a week,
penniless with dysentery.

413
00:29:50,205 --> 00:29:52,081
You're my hero.

414
00:30:05,804 --> 00:30:07,180
Hey.

415
00:30:08,765 --> 00:30:11,309
If you stay,
we'll go out for lndian every night.

416
00:30:13,395 --> 00:30:15,271
You never asked me to stay.

417
00:30:21,570 --> 00:30:23,446
Go, go, go.

418
00:30:43,550 --> 00:30:45,176
You know what's funny?

419
00:30:45,344 --> 00:30:48,971
This is the first time in my life
there's no one waiting at home for me.

420
00:30:49,139 --> 00:30:51,015
I don't even have a home
to come back to.

421
00:30:51,183 --> 00:30:52,516
Oh, God. You'll make friends.

422
00:30:52,684 --> 00:30:54,810
You'll make friends with a backpack,
of course.

423
00:30:54,978 --> 00:30:56,437
It'd be great to get away.

424
00:30:56,605 --> 00:31:00,775
Andy and l were talking about getting
a little villa in Florence for a month.

425
00:31:00,943 --> 00:31:03,611
You know, and in 1 0 years,
when Jack is older....

426
00:31:04,613 --> 00:31:05,947
What?

427
00:31:08,033 --> 00:31:10,952
You know why l was giving you
such a hard time?

428
00:31:12,204 --> 00:31:15,706
I love my job, my guy and my kid,
but....

429
00:31:17,626 --> 00:31:19,627
I wish I could go.

430
00:31:28,804 --> 00:31:30,304
I love you and l'm proud of you.

431
00:31:31,306 --> 00:31:32,848
Now go.

432
00:31:56,456 --> 00:31:58,332
There is a wonderful
old Italian joke...

433
00:31:58,500 --> 00:32:00,835
...about a poor man
who goes to church every day...

434
00:32:01,003 --> 00:32:05,339
...and prays before the statue
of a great saint, begging:

435
00:32:06,133 --> 00:32:12,138
"Dear saint, please, please, please
let me win the lottery."

436
00:32:12,973 --> 00:32:15,766
Finally, the exasperated statue
comes to life...

437
00:32:15,934 --> 00:32:18,144
...and looks down at the begging man
and says:

438
00:32:18,353 --> 00:32:23,733
"My son, please, please, please
buy a ticket."

439
00:32:24,568 --> 00:32:26,360
So now l get the joke.

440
00:32:26,528 --> 00:32:29,155
And l've got three tickets.

441
00:32:49,634 --> 00:32:52,678
You heat the water on the stove.

442
00:32:54,598 --> 00:32:56,891
So if I want to bathe...?

443
00:32:57,059 --> 00:33:02,063
You put the water in the tub.

444
00:33:04,483 --> 00:33:06,400
Okay.

445
00:33:06,735 --> 00:33:13,157
Yeah. lt doesn't really seem like
enough water to bathe in.

446
00:33:15,243 --> 00:33:17,745
Not enough.

447
00:33:17,913 --> 00:33:19,663
Yes, it's enough.

448
00:33:19,831 --> 00:33:23,209
Fill it up three, four, five times.

449
00:33:23,710 --> 00:33:26,921
Everything that's important
gets cleaned.

450
00:33:43,146 --> 00:33:45,606
Is this safe? This...

451
00:33:46,858 --> 00:33:49,110
...scaffolding? Scaffol--

452
00:33:49,277 --> 00:33:51,278
It holds up the ceiling.

453
00:33:51,446 --> 00:33:54,657
Otherwise it will fall apart.

454
00:33:55,325 --> 00:33:56,951
Everything falls apart, my dear.

455
00:33:57,119 --> 00:34:01,789
The only thing permanent in life
is family.

456
00:34:05,877 --> 00:34:07,086
You're not married.

457
00:34:08,255 --> 00:34:10,214
No, divorziata.

458
00:34:10,632 --> 00:34:12,258
Why divorced?

459
00:34:16,179 --> 00:34:17,596
We broke it.

460
00:34:20,642 --> 00:34:23,144
You're more happy now?

461
00:34:27,524 --> 00:34:29,108
I have one rule.

462
00:34:29,651 --> 00:34:34,822
No strange men spending the night.

463
00:34:34,990 --> 00:34:37,700
You American girls
when you come to ltaly...

464
00:34:37,868 --> 00:34:40,202
...all you want is pasta...

465
00:34:40,370 --> 00:34:42,413
...and sausage.

466
00:34:47,252 --> 00:34:48,335
I'll take it.

467
00:34:48,670 --> 00:34:49,962
Good. You chose well.

468
00:35:24,164 --> 00:35:25,206
Cappuccino.

469
00:35:25,373 --> 00:35:28,542
-lt's a zoo in here.
-And my ltalian sucks.

470
00:35:28,710 --> 00:35:31,212
-How long have you been here?
-Two weeks. You?

471
00:35:31,379 --> 00:35:33,297
Six weeks. You'll get better.

472
00:35:33,965 --> 00:35:35,216
Two cappuccinos, please.

473
00:35:35,383 --> 00:35:37,092
And warm the milk this time.

474
00:35:37,260 --> 00:35:39,303
Yesterday it was too hot
and burned my tongue.

475
00:35:39,930 --> 00:35:41,764
-You like Napoleons?
-Of course.

476
00:35:41,932 --> 00:35:44,308
And two Napoleons, please.

477
00:35:45,060 --> 00:35:47,144
Your Italian is fantastic.

478
00:35:47,312 --> 00:35:50,689
I have a wonderful tutor.
I'll give you his number if you like.

479
00:35:50,857 --> 00:35:53,442
-He's really good and he needs work.
-Oh, great.

480
00:35:53,610 --> 00:35:55,527
Are you Dutch? German?

481
00:35:55,695 --> 00:35:59,323
Swedish. Even colder people,
if you can imagine.

482
00:35:59,991 --> 00:36:02,868
-l'm Liz, by the way.
