00:58:39,141 --> 00:58:41,267
Now, before we eat, everyone...

729
00:58:41,435 --> 00:58:44,395
...it is Thanksgiving,
so let us give thanks.

730
00:58:44,563 --> 00:58:47,273
-Yeah. Come on, join hands.
-Okay.

731
00:58:47,441 --> 00:58:49,567
So we just say what we....

732
00:58:50,027 --> 00:58:53,654
What we thank God for tonight.
Sofi, why don't you start?

733
00:58:56,283 --> 00:58:59,452
I am grateful for you, Liz...

734
00:59:00,037 --> 00:59:03,956
...for helping me appreciate life...

735
00:59:04,374 --> 00:59:07,460
...with all that comes with it...

736
00:59:08,462 --> 00:59:11,213
...muffin tops and bad times.

737
00:59:11,673 --> 00:59:12,923
And for Giovanni...

738
00:59:13,592 --> 00:59:16,052
...for making me feel...

739
00:59:16,219 --> 00:59:17,803
...loved and secure.

740
00:59:20,140 --> 00:59:21,641
And Giulio.

741
00:59:21,808 --> 00:59:25,686
Me, l'm grateful for
my beautiful family.

742
00:59:25,854 --> 00:59:28,230
My two little daughters and my wife.

743
00:59:28,398 --> 00:59:32,735
I thank God and the Holy Virgin...

744
00:59:32,903 --> 00:59:34,904
...for this very, very special day.

745
00:59:35,238 --> 00:59:38,991
And for this beautiful family...

746
00:59:39,451 --> 00:59:40,910
...that today is so much bigger.

747
00:59:42,371 --> 00:59:43,496
Very much bigger.

748
00:59:48,502 --> 00:59:52,505
I thank you all for this new custom
of celebration.

749
00:59:52,673 --> 00:59:55,257
And Liz's stuffing...

750
00:59:55,842 --> 00:59:57,385
...and God...

751
00:59:57,552 --> 00:59:59,845
...for my sexiness.

752
01:00:03,392 --> 01:00:04,433
And you, Ruffina?

753
01:00:08,689 --> 01:00:11,524
I thank God for...

754
01:00:11,692 --> 01:00:13,526


755
01:00:17,739 --> 01:00:19,824
Go ahead. Giovanni.

756
01:00:19,991 --> 01:00:22,493
I thank God for...

757
01:00:24,371 --> 01:00:25,329
...fear...

758
01:00:25,497 --> 01:00:29,375
...because for the first time...

759
01:00:30,252 --> 01:00:33,087
...l'm afraid the person next to me...

760
01:00:33,630 --> 01:00:36,173
...will be the one who wants to leave.

761
01:00:41,722 --> 01:00:43,431
Liz?

762
01:00:45,517 --> 01:00:50,187
Well, this all makes me so grateful.

763
01:00:51,523 --> 01:00:53,566
Seeing all you happy people...

764
01:00:53,734 --> 01:00:57,278
...who know how to love each other
and take care of each other.

765
01:00:59,156 --> 01:01:03,200
I look at the amazing women l've met
who l admire so much...

766
01:01:03,368 --> 01:01:08,456
...and the great men,
taking care of their women...

767
01:01:08,623 --> 01:01:11,459
...and putting their children to bed.

768
01:01:12,961 --> 01:01:15,296
I just feel happy...

769
01:01:15,797 --> 01:01:19,467
...to see it and to be part of it.

770
01:01:24,222 --> 01:01:27,308
I'm the luckiest girl in the world.

771
01:02:55,063 --> 01:02:57,565
It's a good breakfast, huh?

772
01:04:22,734 --> 01:04:24,944
I will take this to your room.

773
01:04:30,075 --> 01:04:31,951
It has already started.

774
01:05:17,789 --> 01:05:20,958
-l fell asleep.
-Yeah. Pity.

775
01:05:21,126 --> 01:05:25,337
Probably the only person in the world
who ever fell asleep during meditation.

776
01:05:32,971 --> 01:05:36,557
-This leads to the meditation garden.
-ls the guru here?

777
01:05:36,725 --> 01:05:40,102
-She's always here.
-l know, but is she "here" here?

778
01:05:40,270 --> 01:05:42,354
She's at her ashram in New York.

779
01:05:42,522 --> 01:05:44,898
But l came from New York
to see her here.

780
01:05:45,066 --> 01:05:47,735
Sounds like one of her little tricks.

781
01:05:51,364 --> 01:05:53,741
The meditation cave.

782
01:05:53,950 --> 01:05:58,954
It's open 24/7
and it's air-conditioned.

783
01:06:06,588 --> 01:06:08,464
Corella?

784
01:06:08,757 --> 01:06:12,468
-This is Liz Gilbert.
-Hi. Nice to meet you.

785
01:06:16,097 --> 01:06:19,433
-Where did you get that button?
-They sell them in the bookstore.

786
01:06:19,601 --> 01:06:23,187
That is exactly what I need. I need
something like that. l don't listen.

787
01:06:23,354 --> 01:06:26,273
I never have. My mom used to
call me Little Miss Chatty Cathy...

788
01:06:26,441 --> 01:06:28,358
...because I just ramble.
I am a rambler.

789
01:06:28,526 --> 01:06:31,403
I am rambling now. l'm sorry.

790
01:06:32,113 --> 01:06:34,114
Silence is a wonderful
spiritual practice...

791
01:06:34,282 --> 01:06:38,077
...but if Corella could speak, she'd tell
you it's more challenging than it looks.

792
01:06:38,244 --> 01:06:41,121
-Wait till you've been here for a while.
-Okay.

793
01:06:53,301 --> 01:06:56,136
Thank you, Corella.
I'll be sure to tell her.

794
01:06:56,304 --> 01:06:58,639
-What did she say?
-No idea.

795
01:06:58,807 --> 01:07:01,475
Change into your work clothes.
I'll take you to your seva.

796
01:07:01,643 --> 01:07:04,311
It's a Hindu word
for "selfless devotional work."

797
01:07:04,479 --> 01:07:08,524
-lt's required of everyone who stays.
-Okay. Thank you.

798
01:07:35,176 --> 01:07:38,679
Is there anything in this world skinnier
than an lndian teenage boy?

799
01:07:41,266 --> 01:07:43,142
-l'm Tulsi.
-Liz.

800
01:07:43,685 --> 01:07:44,852
Where are you from?

801
01:07:45,019 --> 01:07:48,981
The next town. My parents have been
devotees of the guru for many years.

802
01:07:49,149 --> 01:07:50,524
We spend a lot of time here.

803
01:07:50,692 --> 01:07:52,359
But...

804
01:07:52,569 --> 01:07:55,946
...they are trying to marry me off.
That's the custom.

805
01:07:56,114 --> 01:08:00,492
-That's not what you want?
-No way. lt sucks.

806
01:08:05,373 --> 01:08:10,210
I want to study psychology, just as our
guru did when she attended college.

807
01:08:10,587 --> 01:08:13,547
I prefer to be with God
than boys my age.

808
01:08:13,715 --> 01:08:17,342
No one in my family understands
my coming all the way to India.

809
01:08:17,886 --> 01:08:21,847
Do you ever look at them and wonder,
"What am I doing in this family?"

810
01:08:22,849 --> 01:08:24,224
You have no idea.

811
01:08:51,002 --> 01:08:55,589
The Guru Gita is an ancient text
1 82 verses long.

812
01:08:55,798 --> 01:08:58,884
In it, the goddess Parvati
is asking Shiva, or God...

813
01:08:59,427 --> 01:09:01,261
...for the secrets of fulfillment.

814
01:09:02,472 --> 01:09:05,474
It's said to have
transforming qualities.

815
01:09:05,934 --> 01:09:09,311
I would just like to take a risk here
and say....

816
01:09:09,479 --> 01:09:13,690
Me and Guru Gita,
we just do not get along.

817
01:09:14,359 --> 01:09:16,693
-What is it you have trouble with?
-Everything.

818
01:09:16,986 --> 01:09:19,988
It's long, it's tedious,
I can't keep up...

819
01:09:20,156 --> 01:09:24,993
...and l get these insane anxieties
about everything in my life...

820
01:09:25,161 --> 01:09:26,912
...and l've lost my place.

821
01:09:27,121 --> 01:09:28,997
Sounds like it has a positive effect...

822
01:09:29,165 --> 01:09:32,584
...if you're having such strong
emotions and physical reactions.

823
01:09:34,003 --> 01:09:35,879
You keep trying.

824
01:09:43,805 --> 01:09:46,181
It is most commendable
that you ended your marriage.

825
01:09:46,891 --> 01:09:49,267
You seem like such a
happy, free person now.

826
01:09:49,435 --> 01:09:52,479
I think my ex-husband
would describe me as selfish.

827
01:09:53,773 --> 01:09:57,150
You mustn't be angry with yourself
or disappointed.

828
01:09:57,318 --> 01:10:01,321
You don't have to make children
or be married to have a family.

829
01:10:03,324 --> 01:10:06,159
Oh, man. They got mosquitoes
here big enough...

830
01:10:06,327 --> 01:10:08,662
...to stand flat-footed
and screw a chicken.

831
01:10:09,998 --> 01:10:12,165
-l love you.
-Liz, have you met...

832
01:10:12,333 --> 01:10:14,668
-...Richard from Texas?
-Hello, Richard from Texas.

833
01:10:14,836 --> 01:10:17,170
-Nice to meet you, Groceries.
-Groceries?

834
01:10:17,338 --> 01:10:20,507
Yeah. Yeah, l heard you eating
before l saw you.

835
01:10:20,717 --> 01:10:23,510
I never seen anybody
eat so much at one time.

836
01:10:23,720 --> 01:10:26,013
You sure do enjoy your groceries.

837
01:10:26,764 --> 01:10:30,809
You know, it's been a rough day,
and if no one takes it personally...

838
01:10:30,977 --> 01:10:34,813
...l'm going to take my large meal
someplace else to eat it in silence.

839
01:10:34,981 --> 01:10:37,149
Oh, no, stay. I'm done.

840
01:10:41,529 --> 01:10:43,655
Looked like you were
working through some...

841
01:10:43,823 --> 01:10:46,491
...pretty rough stuff this morning.

842
01:10:46,659 --> 01:10:48,535
Stuff with your ex-husband?

843
01:10:49,370 --> 01:10:51,496
I got an ex-wife.

844
01:10:52,123 --> 01:10:55,167
She thinks l changed my name
to "Motherfucker."

845
01:10:58,546 --> 01:11:00,380
I--

846
01:11:00,882 --> 01:11:05,886
I just spent some time in Rome
and l came here feeling so great.

847
01:11:06,054 --> 01:11:09,514
And now here l am, at the source...

848
01:11:09,682 --> 01:11:12,559
...and l feel more disconnected
than ever.

849
01:11:13,394 --> 01:11:15,020
Why'd you come here?

850
01:11:16,564 --> 01:11:17,898
I just want some peace.

851
01:11:18,483 --> 01:11:20,233
Peace?

852
01:11:21,861 --> 01:11:24,529
You wanna get
to the castle, Groceries...

853
01:11:24,697 --> 01:11:26,281
...you got to swim the moat.

854
01:11:29,577 --> 01:11:32,579
Here, you can finish that.
I know you can.

855
01:11:39,003 --> 01:11:40,087
Okay.

856
01:11:40,588 --> 01:11:44,299
Simply empty your mind.

857
01:11:44,801 --> 01:11:45,926
Breathe.

858
01:11:47,929 --> 01:11:51,389
What am l going to do
when this year is over?

859
01:11:51,557 --> 01:11:53,266
Where am I going to live?

860
01:11:53,434 --> 01:11:54,726
Well, maybe Chicago.

861
01:11:55,812 --> 01:11:59,397
Oh, my God.
I could build a meditation room--

862
01:11:59,565 --> 01:12:03,568
No. Stop thinking.
Why is this so hard?

863
01:12:09,242 --> 01:12:11,743
Screw you, Corella.
How the hell does she do this?

864
01:12:11,911 --> 01:12:14,538
She looks like
frigging Mother Teresa.

865
01:12:16,833 --> 01:12:19,459
Oh, my God, kill me.

866
01:12:22,547 --> 01:12:24,131
-Who's in the moat today?
-Shut up.

867
01:12:24,340 --> 01:12:26,466
Sounds like you wrestled
some big-ass crocs.

868
01:12:26,634 --> 01:12:29,886
You know what? lf you're so goddamn
smart, what are you doing here?

869
01:12:30,054 --> 01:12:31,972
If you're here,
it makes you smart already.

870
01:12:32,140 --> 01:12:35,433
-Do you wanna talk about what--?
-No, not to you. Thank you.

871
01:12:35,601 --> 01:12:38,645
I'm the only one here. You're gonna
talk about it sooner or later.

872
01:12:38,855 --> 01:12:39,938
I cannot focus in there.

873
01:12:40,106 --> 01:12:44,359
All I think about is my meditation room
and how to decorate.

874
01:12:46,320 --> 01:12:47,487
Are you shitting me?

875
01:12:48,322 --> 01:12:49,322
Are you kidding me?

876
01:12:49,490 --> 01:12:52,826
The meditation room is within,
Groceries. Decorate that.

877
01:12:52,994 --> 01:12:54,786
Do you always talk
in bumper sticker?

878
01:12:54,954 --> 01:12:56,329
I do, and here's another one.

879
01:12:56,497 --> 01:12:59,499
You have to learn to select
your thoughts the way you select...

880
01:12:59,667 --> 01:13:02,502
...your clothes every day.
That's a power you can cultivate.

881
01:13:02,670 --> 01:13:05,922
You wanna come here and control
your life so bad, work on the mind.

882
01:13:06,090 --> 01:13:07,966
That's the only thing
you should control.

883
01:13:08,134 --> 01:13:10,802
If you can't master your thoughts,
you're in trouble.

884
01:13:10,970 --> 01:13:12,012
I am trying.

885
01:13:12,180 --> 01:13:15,182
Yeah, hello, that's the damn problem.
Stop trying. Surrender.

886
01:13:15,391 --> 01:13:18,852
Go out into the garden
and just sit there and still your mind...

887
01:13:19,020 --> 01:13:20,520
...and you watch what happens.

888
01:13:20,688 --> 01:13:22,522
Why don't you just let it be?

889
01:13:24,525 --> 01:13:27,027
Has anyone ever told you
you look like James Taylor?

890
01:13:31,657 --> 01:13:32,908
Every day.

891
01:13:39,916 --> 01:13:42,083
God, he really does.

892
01:13:47,215 --> 01:13:48,882
My prayers were always the same.

893
01:13:49,050 --> 01:13:53,220
"Please, God, please.
Open my heart, send me a sign...

894
01:13:53,429 --> 01:13:57,140
...because we both know
I ain't the sharpest tool in the shed."

895
01:13:58,893 --> 01:14:01,228
Look at you,
floating through Calcutta.

896
01:14:01,896 --> 01:14:04,022
Looks like you had
a great meditation.

897
01:14:04,190 --> 01:14:05,899
I probably have malaria now.

898
01:14:06,150 --> 01:14:07,525
The bites will go away.

899
01:14:08,069 --> 01:14:09,903
Eventually everything goes away.

900
01:14:10,071 --> 01:14:12,739
You ever done that, Groceries?
Begged for a sign?

901
01:14:14,742 --> 01:14:16,076
That sounds vaguely familiar.

902
01:14:16,244 --> 01:14:18,703
Be careful what you wish for.
You just might get it.

903
01:14:18,871 --> 01:14:20,080
What is your problem?

904
01:14:20,248 --> 01:14:24,084
Did you fall in love
with the wrong woman or something?

905
01:14:24,752 --> 01:14:26,253
Excuse me, Miss Gilbert.

906
01:14:26,462 --> 01:14:28,588
You have a phone call.

907
01:14:29,840 --> 01:14:32,259
How's the Guru Gita treating you?

908
01:14:32,927 --> 01:14:36,096
Fine. You'd like her.

909
01:14:37,265 --> 01:14:39,683
Did you get my e-mail?

910
01:14:40,393 --> 01:14:44,354
Yeah. l'm sorry l didn't call sooner.

911
01:14:44,522 --> 01:14:45,939
Why didn't you?

912
01:14:46,107 --> 01:14:47,440
Because if l didn't respond...

913
01:14:47,608 --> 01:14:51,611
...we were still having a conversation.
I was still in it.

914
01:14:53,990 --> 01:14:57,993
I'm sorry. We were just bad timing.

915
01:14:59,996 --> 01:15:04,624
I just wanted things to be easy.
We were good when things were easy.

916
01:15:04,792 --> 01:15:09,129
It's not that I need "easy" right now.
I just can't have "so hard."

917
01:15:11,424 --> 01:15:12,507
Well, you sound good.

918
01:15:13,384 --> 01:15:14,801
Stronger.

919
01:15:15,011 --> 01:15:16,303
So do you.

920
01:15:18,014 --> 01:15:19,639
Yeah, well, l'm an actor, Liz.

921
01:15:23,060 --> 01:15:25,020
I got a part.

922
01:15:27,023 --> 01:15:30,150
It's off-Broadway,
but it's pretty cool.

923
01:15:30,318 --> 01:15:32,485
I'm happy for you.

924
01:15:34,447 --> 01:15:36,156
All right.

925
01:15:36,324 --> 01:15:38,825
Well, l'll see you around, kid.

926
01:16:05,770 --> 01:16:06,853
Check you out.

927
01:16:07,063 --> 01:16:10,065
I have never seen you so focused.

928
01:16:22,078 --> 01:16:23,203
You need a Thums Up.

929
01:16:26,582 --> 01:16:29,876
No, no. No lips on the bottle.

930
01:16:30,086 --> 01:16:32,837
First rule in lndia is never
touch anything but yourself.

931
01:16:37,093 --> 01:16:41,513
Oh, good God. That's, like,
five times sweeter than Coke.

932
01:16:45,559 --> 01:16:48,395
I think it might have
methamphetamines in it.

933
01:16:49,230 --> 01:16:51,147
We can only hope.

934
01:16:54,735 --> 01:16:56,069
I know you feel awful.

935
01:16:57,571 --> 01:16:59,864
But your life's changing.

936
01:17:00,032 --> 01:17:02,242
That's not a bad thing.

937
01:17:02,410 --> 01:17:06,037
And you're in the perfect place for it.
Surrounded by grace.

938
01:17:06,997 --> 01:17:11,209
I thought I was over him, but...

939
01:17:11,877 --> 01:17:12,919
...l love him.

940
01:17:13,379 --> 01:17:14,421
Big deal.

941
01:17:14,630 --> 01:17:17,090
-So you fell in love with someone.
-l really miss him.

942
01:17:17,258 --> 01:17:18,758
So miss him.

943
01:17:18,926 --> 01:17:22,637
Send him some light and love every
time you think of him, then drop it.

944
01:17:23,431 --> 01:17:27,183
You know, if you could clear out
all that space in your mind...

945
01:17:27,351 --> 01:17:29,436
...that you're using
to obsess over this guy...

946
01:17:29,645 --> 01:17:32,939
...and your failed marriage,
you'd have a vacuum with a doorway.

947
01:17:33,149 --> 01:17:36,276
And you know what the universe
would do with that doorway?

948
01:17:37,570 --> 01:17:40,947
Rush in. God would rush in.

949
01:17:41,157 --> 01:17:46,286
Fill you with more love
than you ever dreamed of. Man.

950
01:17:50,416 --> 01:17:52,292
Groceries.

951
01:17:52,460 --> 01:17:56,796
I think you have the capacity someday
to love the whole world.

952
01:18:02,178 --> 01:18:04,304
What do they sell over there?

953
01:18:09,810 --> 01:18:13,313
Ganesh. Remover of obstacles.

954
01:18:16,066 --> 01:18:17,859
I'm gonna need a lot of these.

955
01:18:18,027 --> 01:18:22,655
Speaking of elephants, there's a rogue
elephant on the loose in the area.

956
01:18:22,990 --> 01:18:24,324
He was with carnival.

957
01:18:24,492 --> 01:18:28,119
They say he is very,
very unpredictable and volatile.

958
01:18:28,287 --> 01:18:30,371
That just makes him more attractive
to her.

959
01:18:30,539 --> 01:18:33,500
How'd you get to be so smart?
I'll bet it was the hard way.

960
01:18:33,667 --> 01:18:34,876
Don't change the subject.

961
01:18:35,628 --> 01:18:39,756
Well, when is this grieving phase
going to pass?

962
01:18:39,924 --> 01:18:42,258
You want a day on a calendar
you can circle?

963
01:18:42,426 --> 01:18:45,345
-Can you give me one?
-No. You got to do the work.

964
01:18:45,513 --> 01:18:48,181
Meditate and go to seva...

965
01:18:48,349 --> 01:18:51,559
...and most important, get your butt
down to the Geet every morning...

966
01:18:51,727 --> 01:18:53,019
...and something'll change.

967
01:18:53,187 --> 01:18:57,190
I just cannot get through the Guru Gita.
I can't find that feeling of devotion.

968
01:18:57,358 --> 01:19:01,444
Okay. Devotion's love. Pick somebody
or something you wanna devote it to.

969
01:19:01,612 --> 01:19:04,864
It doesn't have to be the guru.
It's all the same to her.

970
01:19:05,032 --> 01:19:07,242
This is about you.

971
01:19:08,786 --> 01:19:13,540
Can l tell you something, Groceries?
You got some serious control issues.

972
01:19:13,707 --> 01:19:15,542
Is it obvious?

973
01:19:15,709 --> 01:19:19,671
All right, Richard,
get out from inside my head now.

974
01:19:19,838 --> 01:19:20,880
Shut the door.

975
01:19:23,342 --> 01:19:26,052
-That's him?
-That's him.

976
01:19:26,554 --> 01:19:31,224
-He's hideous.
-No, he's not. He's cute.

977
01:19:31,392 --> 01:19:32,767
He's a Sagittarius.

978
01:19:33,394 --> 01:19:35,353
He studies computer programming
in Delhi.

979
01:19:35,521 --> 01:19:37,355
He has very good grades.

980
01:19:37,523 --> 01:19:40,900
And his family is very, very wealthy.

981
01:19:41,569 --> 01:19:46,906
He will be very conceited
and dictatorial.

982
01:19:48,075 --> 01:19:49,909
My life is over at 1 7.

983
01:19:56,917 --> 01:19:58,793
Tulsi.

984
01:22:34,908 --> 01:22:37,243
Ladies and gentlemen,
welcome to the dance floor...

985
01:22:37,411 --> 01:22:40,580
...for their very first couples dance,
Liz and Stephen.

986
01:22:53,093 --> 01:22:54,969
My people.

987
01:22:55,596 --> 01:22:56,971
-Are you ready?
-l'm ready.

988
01:22:59,391 --> 01:23:01,434
-You look beautiful.
-Thank you.

989
01:23:01,602 --> 01:23:03,936
I married a hottie.

990
01:23:06,315 --> 01:23:09,358
-What is that? That's not our song.
-No, it is not.

991
01:23:09,526 --> 01:23:11,110
Baby, that's not our song.

992
01:23:11,278 --> 01:23:13,780
-Definitely not.
-Everybody's looking at us.

993
01:23:13,989 --> 01:23:17,241
It's okay. I'm gonna go talk to the guy.
It's gonna be fine.

994
01:23:28,629 --> 01:23:31,088
-l told you l'd get it.
-This is taking care of it?

995
01:24:29,189 --> 01:24:33,150
I owe you a wedding gift.
I didn't know what was appropriate.

996
01:24:35,696 --> 01:24:38,573
I wanted to tell you l've been...

997
01:24:38,949 --> 01:24:41,075
...dedicating my Guru Gita to you.

998
01:24:43,120 --> 01:24:46,873
Imagining you happy
is what got me through it.

999
01:24:49,877 --> 01:24:52,044
What did it look like...

1000
01:24:52,212 --> 01:24:54,380
...when I was happy?

1001
01:24:58,010 --> 01:25:01,304
I imagine you and Rijul...

1002
01:25:01,471 --> 01:25:04,473
...smiling and looking
at each other...

1003
01:25:05,392 --> 01:25:07,852
...with love and kindness.

1004
01:25:08,645 --> 01:25:11,397
It seemed very real.

1005
01:25:13,817 --> 01:25:16,235
Thank you so much, Liz.

1006
01:25:17,237 --> 01:25:20,197
That helps me to believe it as well.

1007
01:25:36,548 --> 01:25:38,925
Thinking about your own wedding?

1008
01:25:39,676 --> 01:25:41,427
Yeah, me too.

1009
01:25:41,637 --> 01:25:45,431
The funny thing about weddings,
you end up thinking about yourself.

1010
01:25:46,308 --> 01:25:51,228
Did you throw yourself a big shindig?
Big, white, floppy dress?

1011
01:25:51,855 --> 01:25:57,610
Yep. l arranged it all.
Nobody forced me into anything.

1012
01:25:57,778 --> 01:26:00,237
Yeah. And now
you can't forgive yourself.

1013
01:26:00,405 --> 01:26:04,784
Honestly, I'm waiting for him
to forgive me.

1014
01:26:04,952 --> 01:26:06,452
To release me.

1015
01:26:06,662 --> 01:26:09,747
Waiting for him to forgive you
is a damn waste of time, Groceries.

1016
01:26:09,915 --> 01:26:11,791
Forgive yourself.

1017
01:26:13,085 --> 01:26:15,294
It's not that easy.

1018
01:26:16,630 --> 01:26:18,130
Yeah.

1019
01:26:33,814 --> 01:26:35,106
Good night, Richard.

1020
01:26:35,440 --> 01:26:37,775
-Follow me.
-l'm tired.

1021
01:26:38,151 --> 01:26:39,443
Get your butt up here.

1022
01:27:06,430 --> 01:27:08,848
It's not a pretty story...

1023
01:27:09,808 --> 01:27:11,976
...but it's pretty classic.

1024
01:27:12,728 --> 01:27:18,149
Too much alcohol, too many drugs,
too much mindless cheating.

1025
01:27:19,943 --> 01:27:21,819
Just regret.

1026
01:27:24,448 --> 01:27:26,699
Ocean of regret.

1027
01:27:29,036 --> 01:27:31,370
I lost everything.

1028
01:27:32,122 --> 01:27:34,540
My pride, my job.

1029
01:27:35,333 --> 01:27:37,209
My family.

1030
01:27:39,880 --> 01:27:42,006
I lost my family.

1031
01:27:53,894 --> 01:27:58,397
One day after work, l stopped off
at a bar and I got shitfaced.

1032
01:27:59,066 --> 01:28:01,484
I was a lot like you, you know.

1033
01:28:01,651 --> 01:28:05,237
I was just-- I don't know.
I thought too much, I felt too....

1034
01:28:06,782 --> 01:28:09,283
I wanted to feel nothing.

1035
01:28:12,370 --> 01:28:14,205
I should've called a cab, but I didn't.

1036
01:28:14,372 --> 01:28:17,625
I just got in my car
and l drove home.

1037
01:28:21,588 --> 01:28:23,506
My little boy....

1038
01:28:28,512 --> 01:28:31,555
He was 8 years old at the time.
He was pl--

1039
01:28:36,228 --> 01:28:41,190
He was sitting in the driveway with his
little Hot Wheels, waiting for his lost...

1040
01:28:41,358 --> 01:28:43,776
...drunk, miserable dad...

1041
01:28:44,945 --> 01:28:47,738
...to come home and play with him.

1042
01:28:49,324 --> 01:28:51,325
I didn't see him.

1043
01:28:52,244 --> 01:28:57,623
I didn't. I just roared into that driveway
and l didn't see my little boy.

1044
01:28:59,084 --> 01:29:01,710
But he-- No, he....

1045
01:29:03,130 --> 01:29:05,256
He got out of the way.

1046
01:29:09,970 --> 01:29:12,888
He was used to getting out of the way
when l was around.

1047
01:29:14,224 --> 01:29:15,933
And l-- You know, I don't--

1048
01:29:16,101 --> 01:29:17,893
I don't know.
I don't remember a thing.

1049
01:29:18,061 --> 01:29:20,771
Next day, l woke up
and they were gone.

1050
01:29:22,399 --> 01:29:27,319
My wife had been watching
what happened out the window.

1051
01:29:28,155 --> 01:29:29,989
She just wasn't gonna....

1052
01:29:31,825 --> 01:29:34,368
She just wasn't gonna
do it anymore.

1053
01:29:35,495 --> 01:29:37,163
So....

1054
01:29:41,835 --> 01:29:43,586
He's 1 8 now.

1055
01:29:43,753 --> 01:29:47,381
He's in school and,
oh, God, he's so smart.

1056
01:29:52,637 --> 01:29:55,639
God, he's so funny and he's....

1057
01:29:58,185 --> 01:30:00,186
He's so sweet.

1058
01:30:06,526 --> 01:30:08,444
I missed it all.

1059
01:30:08,612 --> 01:30:10,487
I missed...

1060
01:30:12,365 --> 01:30:15,784
...my son's growing up. Just missed it.

1061
01:30:28,798 --> 01:30:30,549
Okay?

1062
01:30:33,178 --> 01:30:34,720
Come here.

1063
01:30:42,729 --> 01:30:43,729
Here's the deal.

1064
01:30:44,564 --> 01:30:47,399
You're gonna stay here
till you forgive yourself.

1065
01:30:47,567 --> 01:30:49,443
You hear me?

1066
01:30:50,570 --> 01:30:53,447
Everything else
will take care of itself.

1067
01:30:54,741 --> 01:30:57,576
Is this where you forgave yourself?

1068
01:31:00,914 --> 01:31:03,582
I'm trying, Elizabeth.

1069
01:31:03,750 --> 01:31:05,960
I am trying.

1070
01:31:54,634 --> 01:31:56,218
Hey.

1071
01:31:58,888 --> 01:32:02,808
I believe this is the song they were
supposed to play at our wedding.

1072
01:32:39,262 --> 01:32:41,805
I did love you, Stephen.

1073
01:32:48,563 --> 01:32:50,356
I know.

1074
01:32:52,817 --> 01:32:55,319
But l still love you.

1075
01:33:04,704 --> 01:33:06,789
So love me.

1076
01:33:12,379 --> 01:33:14,546
But l miss you.

1077
01:33:18,009 --> 01:33:20,302
So miss me.

1078
01:33:21,304 --> 01:33:25,641
Send me love and light
every time you think of me...

1079
01:33:25,809 --> 01:33:27,059
...then drop it.

1080
01:33:45,620 --> 01:33:48,205
It won't last forever.

1081
01:33:49,874 --> 01:33:52,000
Nothing does.

1082
01:34:11,312 --> 01:34:13,397
-Bye-bye.
-Goodbye, Mr. Richard.

1083
01:34:13,565 --> 01:34:15,441
I'll see you.

1084
01:34:16,317 --> 01:34:19,778
Now that you're going,
who is gonna kick my ass every day?

1085
01:34:19,946 --> 01:34:23,782
Oh, l'd stay till a monsoon
swept me away if I could. Bye-bye.

1086
01:34:23,950 --> 01:34:26,201
But you've got bills to pay
and houses to build.

1087
01:34:26,369 --> 01:34:29,455
You just keep doing the work
and move on with your life, will you?

1088
01:34:29,622 --> 01:34:32,291
The man is getting on a plane
and you're still bossing me.

1089
01:34:32,459 --> 01:34:37,921
I've got your whole list: move on,
use mosquito repellent and....

1090
01:34:38,089 --> 01:34:41,258
I don't know. There were some
other things. I wrote them down.

1091
01:34:45,889 --> 01:34:48,599
Go back to Texas, Richard.

1092
01:34:57,567 --> 01:35:00,486
Well, l ain't getting
any prettier standing here.

1093
01:35:02,906 --> 01:35:04,114
So l'm off.

1094
01:35:14,167 --> 01:35:16,126
Hey, Groceries.

1095
01:35:16,628 --> 01:35:17,836
Believe in love again.

1096
01:35:41,736 --> 01:35:44,196
Liz. Liz, l've just taken
my badge off today.

1097
01:35:44,364 --> 01:35:47,366
I've done so well.
Four weeks of silence. lt was so dull.

1098
01:35:47,534 --> 01:35:49,910
But it's like a facelift
because your face...

1099
01:35:50,078 --> 01:35:54,790
...you know, just relaxes and your
throat just drops down. It's a bargain.

1100
01:35:54,958 --> 01:35:56,542
We've got so much to catch up on.

1101
01:35:59,796 --> 01:36:05,342
Oh, golly. Good for you.
You will get so much out of that.

1102
01:36:05,885 --> 01:36:09,346
And your throat will look amazing
as well.

1103
01:36:13,309 --> 01:36:14,518
Excuse me, Elizabeth.

1104
01:36:14,686 --> 01:36:17,563
They're asking you to report
to the seva office after dinner...

1105
01:36:17,772 --> 01:36:19,064
...if you don't mind.

1106
01:36:19,691 --> 01:36:22,067
We're taking you off
the floor-scrubbing team.

1107
01:36:22,277 --> 01:36:25,737
There are about 50 devotees arriving
tomorrow from all over the world...

1108
01:36:25,905 --> 01:36:29,408
...for a 1 0-day retreat and we'd
like you to be the key hostess.

1109
01:36:29,909 --> 01:36:33,078
We ask that you don't take part
during the meditations.

1110
01:36:33,288 --> 01:36:38,083
We need you to watch over the flock,
make sure everyone is all right.

1111
01:36:38,418 --> 01:36:42,379
We call the person who does
this job Little Suzy Cream Cheese.

1112
01:36:42,880 --> 01:36:47,092
You need to be social and bubbly
and smiling all the time.

1113
01:36:50,597 --> 01:36:52,431
Madam...

1114
01:36:52,890 --> 01:36:54,933
...l'm your girl.

1115
01:37:10,116 --> 01:37:12,951
So just find your suitcase,
it should be here somewhere...

1116
01:37:13,119 --> 01:37:15,329
...and then head down the path
to your room.

1117
01:37:16,372 --> 01:37:21,835
So the holy truth of the whole
adventure here in India is in one line:

1118
01:37:22,211 --> 01:37:25,714
God dwells within you as you.

1119
01:37:25,882 --> 01:37:28,133
God's not interested
in watching a performance...

1120
01:37:28,343 --> 01:37:30,636
...of how a spiritual person
looks and behaves.

1121
01:37:30,803 --> 01:37:33,722
The quiet girl who glides silently
through the place...

1122
01:37:33,890 --> 01:37:37,726
...with a gentle, ethereal smile,
who is that person?

1123
01:37:37,894 --> 01:37:42,147
That's lngrid Bergman
in The Bells of St. Mary's, not me.

1124
01:37:42,357 --> 01:37:46,652
God dwells within me as me.

1125
01:38:55,930 --> 01:38:58,223
Child tormented by demon.

1126
01:39:05,231 --> 01:39:06,982
It looks like teething.

1127
01:39:07,150 --> 01:39:09,067
Same thing.

1128
01:39:12,447 --> 01:39:14,072
Your turn.

1129
01:39:19,954 --> 01:39:21,246
Hello, Ketut.

1130
01:39:22,039 --> 01:39:23,540
I'm very happy to meet you.

1131
01:39:24,959 --> 01:39:26,585
You are a world traveler.

1132
01:39:27,670 --> 01:39:29,921
No, I came to see you
about a year ago.

1133
01:39:30,590 --> 01:39:33,925
-You girl from California?
-No, I girl from New York.

1134
01:39:35,094 --> 01:39:36,428
Don't remember.

1135
01:39:40,183 --> 01:39:42,434
Well, you told me
I should come back here to Bali.

1136
01:39:42,602 --> 01:39:44,728
You said I could help you
with your English...

1137
01:39:44,896 --> 01:39:47,272
...and you would teach me
the things that you know.

1138
01:39:50,860 --> 01:39:52,611
You gave me this.

1139
01:39:53,488 --> 01:39:55,280
Okay.

1140
01:40:00,620 --> 01:40:03,789
You. You. l remember you.

1141
01:40:03,956 --> 01:40:06,124
-Oh, good.
-You sad girl from New York.

1142
01:40:06,292 --> 01:40:08,919
-Yes.
-You Liss. You came back.

1143
01:40:09,086 --> 01:40:11,129
-l came back.
-You, you, you.

1144
01:40:11,297 --> 01:40:12,422
Me, me, me.

1145
01:40:12,715 --> 01:40:14,633
So long ago we meet.

1146
01:40:14,801 --> 01:40:19,971
Last time, you have too much worry,
too much sorrow.

1147
01:40:20,139 --> 01:40:23,099
Last time,
you look like sad old woman.

1148
01:40:24,227 --> 01:40:26,895
Now you pretty.

1149
01:40:27,063 --> 01:40:29,564
-Why so different?
-Well...

1150
01:40:29,732 --> 01:40:31,983
...a lot of things, really.

1151
01:40:32,151 --> 01:40:34,986
But l was in Rome for four months,
just feeding myself...

1152
01:40:35,154 --> 01:40:37,614
...and then I went to live
at an ashram in lndia.

1153
01:40:37,782 --> 01:40:40,158
Now, we put together.

1154
01:40:40,326 --> 01:40:41,827
Exactly. That's why l'm here.

1155
01:40:41,994 --> 01:40:44,329
-Ketut good for that.
-What'd you give him?

1156
01:40:47,834 --> 01:40:50,335
Do you still want me to help you
with your English?

1157
01:40:50,503 --> 01:40:52,629
English later, Liss.

1158
01:40:52,797 --> 01:40:56,007
First, better idea.

1159
01:41:00,471 --> 01:41:02,514
How old are these?

1160
01:41:02,682 --> 01:41:05,350
From grandfather.
Very important spells.

1161
01:41:05,518 --> 01:41:08,019
Also mantras, cures.

1162
01:41:08,187 --> 01:41:10,438
Thousand years' worth.

1163
01:41:10,606 --> 01:41:14,150
All I have, all l know, right here.

1164
01:41:14,318 --> 01:41:15,485
You copy for me?

1165
01:41:15,653 --> 01:41:17,696
Absolutely. l can go to town
and take these--

1166
01:41:17,864 --> 01:41:19,698
No. You don't take.

1167
01:41:22,952 --> 01:41:25,370
You copy here, better, Liss.

1168
01:41:25,538 --> 01:41:28,081
I take a nap now. l very old.

1169
01:41:30,209 --> 01:41:31,543
How old are you, Ketut?

1170
01:41:31,711 --> 01:41:33,336
One hundred and one...

1171
01:41:33,504 --> 01:41:36,715
...or maybe 64.

1172
01:41:36,883 --> 01:41:39,217
Don't remember.

1173
01:41:47,226 --> 01:41:49,394
This is gonna take me
the rest of my life.

1174
01:41:49,562 --> 01:41:53,231
He make you pretty, find you husband,
you work hard for him.

1175
01:41:53,399 --> 01:41:55,525
That's exactly opposite
of why l'm here.

1176
01:41:55,693 --> 01:41:58,111
Everybody need husband.

1177
01:42:04,118 --> 01:42:05,744
Would you mind getting me water?

1178
01:42:05,912 --> 01:42:07,412
No.

1179
01:42:07,622 --> 01:42:12,250
Fine. Keep making copies.
I get water.

1180
01:42:26,098 --> 01:42:29,434
So, Liz, the Balinese believe
that Bali's the center of the universe.

1181
01:42:29,602 --> 01:42:31,269
And here we are
in the center of Bali.

1182
01:42:31,437 --> 01:42:33,772
You got the one bedroom,
got your fish pond.

1183
01:42:33,940 --> 01:42:35,649
You got your own meditation temple.

1184
01:42:35,942 --> 01:42:38,568
I tell you, since the bombing,
tourism's been way down...

1185
01:42:38,736 --> 01:42:42,197
...so l can give you this place
at a very, very good price right now.

1186
01:42:42,365 --> 01:42:44,282
Paradise.

1187
01:42:47,036 --> 01:42:49,245
-l'll take it.
-People in Bali understand...

1188
01:42:49,413 --> 01:42:52,457
...in order to stay happy,
must always know where you are...

1189
01:42:52,667 --> 01:42:54,125
...every moment.

1190
01:42:54,293 --> 01:42:58,922
Right here is perfect balance.
Right at meeting of heaven and earth.

1191
01:43:00,132 --> 01:43:02,884
Not too much God,
not too much selfish.

1192
01:43:03,052 --> 01:43:06,137
Otherwise, life too crazy.

1193
01:43:06,305 --> 01:43:09,766
You lose balance, you lose power.

1194
01:43:09,934 --> 01:43:13,311
In morning,
you do meditation from India.

1195
01:43:13,813 --> 01:43:15,814
Serious. Very serious.

1196
01:43:15,982 --> 01:43:18,108
In day, you enjoy Bali.

1197
01:43:27,994 --> 01:43:30,996
Then in afternoon, come see me.

1198
01:43:38,212 --> 01:43:40,964
End of day, you do new meditation.

1199
01:43:41,132 --> 01:43:42,173
Very simple.

1200
01:43:42,341 --> 01:43:46,011
Sit in silence and smile.

1201
01:43:47,263 --> 01:43:48,638
I feel balanced already.

1202
01:43:48,806 --> 01:43:50,181
Not so easy, Liss.

1203
01:43:50,349 --> 01:43:55,020
Smile with face. Smile with mind.

1204
01:43:55,229 --> 01:43:58,231
Even smile in liver.

1205
01:44:00,151 --> 01:44:02,527
See you later, alligator.

1206
01:45:15,434 --> 01:45:17,060
Oh, God.

1207
01:45:17,228 --> 01:45:19,437
-Are you all right?
-Are you blind?

1208
01:45:19,605 --> 01:45:24,442
-Please, let me take you to a doctor.
-l'm fine. l just--

1209
01:45:28,114 --> 01:45:29,781
It looks bad.

1210
01:45:29,949 --> 01:45:31,616
Very bad, Liss.

1211
01:45:31,826 --> 01:45:34,953
-What happen?
-This idiot ran me off the road.

1212
01:45:35,162 --> 01:45:36,955
A man? He rich?

1213
01:45:38,290 --> 01:45:39,749
This very hot.

1214
01:45:40,251 --> 01:45:43,294
-You need healer.
-l have you. You're a medicine man.

1215
01:45:43,462 --> 01:45:47,090
-No. You need Wayan.
-Yeah.

1216
