Why you do that?

1621
02:16:07,785 --> 02:16:10,787
I couldn't keep my balance.

1622
02:16:12,289 --> 02:16:16,376
Liss, listen to Ketut.

1623
02:16:16,543 --> 02:16:20,713
Sometimes to lose balance
for love...

1624
02:16:20,881 --> 02:16:25,176
...is part of living balanced life.

1625
02:16:39,316 --> 02:16:41,150
In the end...

1626
02:16:41,318 --> 02:16:46,114
...I've come to believe in something
I call "The Physics of the Quest."

1627
02:16:48,158 --> 02:16:52,996
A force in nature governed by laws
as real as the laws of gravity.

1628
02:16:53,497 --> 02:16:57,000
The rule of Quest Physics
goes something like this:

1629
02:16:57,209 --> 02:17:01,295
If you're brave enough to leave behind
everything familiar and comforting...

1630
02:17:01,463 --> 02:17:04,966
...which can be anything from your
house to bitter, old resentments...

1631
02:17:05,134 --> 02:17:07,677
...and set out
on a truth-seeking journey...

1632
02:17:07,845 --> 02:17:10,805
...either externally or internally...

1633
02:17:10,973 --> 02:17:13,516
...and if you are truly willing
to regard everything...

1634
02:17:13,684 --> 02:17:16,686
...that happens to you on that journey
as a clue...

1635
02:17:16,854 --> 02:17:21,357
...and if you accept everyone you
meet along the way as a teacher...

1636
02:17:25,863 --> 02:17:28,364
...and if you are prepared,
most of all...

1637
02:17:28,532 --> 02:17:32,869
...to face and forgive some
very difficult realities about yourself...

1638
02:17:33,037 --> 02:17:35,371
...then the truth
will not be withheld from you.

1639
02:17:36,040 --> 02:17:37,790
Felipe?

1640
02:17:50,137 --> 02:17:52,388
I can't help but believe it,
given my experience.

1641
02:18:25,756 --> 02:18:28,299
I decided on my word.

1642
02:18:36,433 --> 02:18:38,434
It means:

1643
02:18:40,270 --> 02:18:42,605
"Let's cross over."

